page.title: 07GARANGE FARM
page.content: A small stream in a deep ditch runs east-west across the north part of this area.The ditch is very overgrown, and contains nettles, rosebay willowherb,various grasses and a variety of other wild plants. About 30% of the area is arable farmland. Some of the fields have already been ploughed in preparation for planting winter corn. The rest of the area, about 70%, consists of pasture land. Many of the fields had cattle grazing in them. In the south east corner of the area is a small woodland area with a path running through it. The woodland is dominantly deciduous, with a few conifers. All fields in the area are bordered by well-established hedges, mostly of hawthorn. The hedge showed little sign of having been trimmed for some time.
